50|$|This {{approach}} {{estimates the}} construction {{cost of the}} improvements, as if new, and deducts factors <b>for</b> <b>depreciation,</b> disutility, and external obsolescence. To this is added {{the value of the}} site and site improvements. The result is the value via the cost approach. Comparable data is used to estimate the site value, and may also be useful in estimating construction costs and other factors. In practice, however, most appraisers use standard costing services for cost estimates and use an age-life method <b>for</b> <b>depreciation.</b>|$|R
