50|$|When a {{taxpayer}} sells an asset for a gain after taking deductions <b>for</b> <b>depreciation,</b> depreciation recapture {{is used to}} tax the gain. Because the taxpayer received a deduction from ordinary income <b>for</b> the <b>depreciation</b> of the asset, any gain the taxpayer receives, up to the depreciation amount, must be included as ordinary income to offset the earlier deduction. Any gain above that is a capital gain subject to capital gains tax rates (usually more favorable).|$|R
